{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01Qc9jpEo4AVzFrAkDYwMPcw","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 10 experiments completed. The BLIS E2E results are essentially identical to idea-1's trace replay results (56.2% E2E, 79.4% TTFT, 9.5% ITL), which makes sense — the overhead floor dominates the step-time prediction in BLIS, so the kv_sum coefficient addition doesn't change the BLIS E2E at all.\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n1. **The total-context coefficient has NO impact on BLIS E2E** because the overhead floor (~4-9ms) dominates. For 70-90% of steps (decode-only), GPU compute is ~100-400µs but the overhead floor is ~4000-9000µs. The kv_sum coefficient only matters for the 10-30% of mixed steps where GPU compute exceeds the floor — and even there, the kv_sum contribution is small relative to the floor.\n2. **The 34B anomaly is NOT anomalous in trace replay mode** — CodeLlama-34B errors (53.6-58.9% E2E) are in the same range as other models. The anomaly was a workload-spec-specific artifact.\n3. **KV features have zero signal for llama-2-7b and mixtral-8x7b-v0-1** — kv_sum=0 for all steps. This is because the lifecycle extractor found no active requests overlapping the step windows for these single-experiment models. This needs investigation.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nNow let me write all FINDINGS files and the summary. Let me update the todo list and write everything in parallel."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27497e41-6ff8-42ab-aee1-66206c73fdbf","uuid":"ea393dc0-28df-4b21-85cd-10395b33dc13"}
