{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01TUr8LVDQgRiGXZ3YwAMkgm","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All work for Idea 2 is complete. Here's the summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n## Idea 2: Total-Context Linear Model with Feature Scaling — Completed\n\n### Three Sub-Hypotheses Executed\n\n**H1: FairBatching 3-Coefficient Formulation** — PARTIALLY SUPPORTED\n- 3-coeff OLS (`a + b*new_tokens + c*kv_sum`): **56.2% mean per-step MAPE** — 27pp better than the 83.1% 2-coeff baseline\n- The kv_sum coefficient is positive and stable (0.031-0.065) for models with KV data\n- However, 2/5 models have kv_sum=0 (lifecycle extractor coverage gap)\n\n**H2: Feature Scaling Comparison** — REFUTED  \n- ALL scaling variants (StandardScaler, log-transform, combined) at 83.0-86.0% MAPE are **WORSE** than the no-KV baseline (82.0%)\n- Root cause: **multicollinearity** among 4 KV features, not scale mismatch. The fix is fewer features (H1's approach), not better scaling\n\n**H3: BLIS E2E Validation + 34B Investigation** — REFUTED\n- BLIS E2E: **56.2% mean** (identical to Round 2 trace replay). kv_sum has **zero impact** because the overhead floor dominates\n- ITL: **9.5% mean** (5/10 < 10%) — same as idea-1\n- 34B anomaly resolved: NOT model-specific, was workload-spec-specific\n\n### Key Finding\nThe overhead floor (~4-9ms) masks all step-time prediction improvements. The binding constraint is NOT the step-time model — it's the floor calibration and simulation fidelity. Improving GPU compute prediction (the focus of this idea) cannot improve BLIS E2E while the floor dominates 70-90% of step predictions.\n\n### Artifacts Produced\n- FINDINGS.md for each sub-hypothesis (3 files)\n- FINDINGS_SUMMARY.md with full per-experiment error table\n- Per-model StepML artifacts (5 JSON files) with kv_sum coefficients\n- Go changes patch (22 lines — StepML CLI integration from idea-1)\n- Experiment scripts (`run_h1_h2.py`, `run_h3_blis.py`)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27497e41-6ff8-42ab-aee1-66206c73fdbf","uuid":"4cdc5fcd-c537-4480-a75c-185bab8a3a89"}
